title: Hairpin Accessible Platform - bp Adelaide Grand Final(4 Day Thu - Sun)
description: Hairpin Accessibility Platform Hear the roar of the Supercars lap after lap as they accelerate hard from the final corner of the circuit. This grandstand is located in the middle of the hairpin at Turn 14, providing excellent views of race cars finishing their lap, accelerating off down pit straight, and coming into the pits. Be among the first to know which driver is heading to the pits, as well as when a driver gains a position, as the hairpin is also one of the major passing places on the circuit. . | Please note: Children's Policy: Children 3 years and under admitted for free if they sit on the lap of a full paying adult. Accessible Seating & Companion Card Holder: Accessible seating can be purchased online. Bookings including a Companion Card ticket can only be collected from the Box Office. The Companion Card must be presented upon collection.
organizer: SOUTH AUSTRALIAN MOTOR SPORT BOARD

title: Senna Accessible Platform (Outside) - bp Adelaide Grand Final (4-DAY)
description: Senna Accessibility Platform Located on 'Driver's Left' as they race hard out of Pit Straight, the Senna Accessibility Platform offers one of the Adelaide 500's most iconic viewing locations at the Chicane, particularly at the start of each race. Watch the Supercars bounce over the kerbs as the drivers push their race cars to the limit and become airborne; and hold your breath as two drivers attempt to manoeuvre through this section of the track side by side off the start line as well as at each safety car restart. . | Please note: Children's Policy: Children 3 years and under admitted for free if they sit on the lap of a full paying adult. Accessible Seating & Companion Card Holder: Accessible seating can be purchased online. Bookings including a Companion Card ticket can only be collected from the Box Office. The Companion Card must be presented upon collection.
organizer: SOUTH AUSTRALIAN MOTOR SPORT BOARD

title: Barry Sheene Pit Straight Grandstand - bp Adelaide Grand Final (4-Day)
description: Barry Sheene Pit Straight Grandstand Each Pit Straight Grandstand seat provides pole-position views of not only pit straight but all the action and drama in pit lane. Marvel at the lap-after-lap acceleration and high-speed driving out of the hairpin, and cheer the race winner across the finish line, followed by a great view of the 2024 Champion's celebration post-race. Super Screens ensure ticketholders do not miss a moment of the action with close access to the Gold Zone. . | Please note: Children's Policy: Children 3 years and under admitted for free if they sit on the lap of a full paying adult.
organizer: SOUTH AUSTRALIAN MOTOR SPORT BOARD

title: Senna Chicane Grandstand - bp Adelaide Grand Final (4 Day Thu - Sun)
description: The Senna Chicane Grandstand is one of the most iconic viewing locations providing spectacular views of the on-track battles that come with Supercars racing, particularly at the start of each race. title: Brock Straight Grandstand - bp Adelaide Grand Final(4 Day Thu - Sun)
description: Brock Straight Grandstand Located at the end of Brock Straight and named after Australian motorsport icon Peter Brock, this grandstand offers reserved 4-day covered grandstand seating to view all the thrills and spills at Turn 8. One of the most notorious corners of any Supercars racetrack in Australia. Witness the high-speed approach as drivers throw their cars into the corner at a speed of more than 200km/h. It is rare a single Adelaide 500 has been run and won without at least one driver losing control at this part of the track. . | Please note: Children's Policy: Children 3 years and under admitted for free if they sit on the lap of a full paying adult.
organizer: SOUTH AUSTRALIAN MOTOR SPORT BOARD

title: Pit Entry Grandstand - bp Adelaide Grand Final (4 Day Thu - Sun)
description: Pit Entry The Pit Entry Grandstand provides sweeping views of the final three corners of the Adelaide Street circuit and it's the location where drivers peel off from the race and head into the pits. Watch the drivers struggle to control their Supercars as they bounce into the hairpin under brakes, all while trying to nose their race cars up past their rivals in front or defending their challengers from making a positional pass from behind. . | Please note: Children's Policy: Children 3 years and under admitted for free if they sit on the lap of a full paying adult.
organizer: SOUTH AUSTRALIAN MOTOR SPORT BOARD

title: Brabham Grandstand - bp Adelaide Grand Final (4 Day Thu - Sun)
description: Brabham Grandstand Named after motorsport legend Sir Jack Brabham, this grandstand offers prime views of the high-speed action and mistakes at Turn 8 as well as one of the best passing places on the Adelaide Street Circuit, Turn 9. Watch both extremes of Supercars racing as they hurtle through Australia's most notorious race corner, Turn 8, which has caught out drivers of calibre such as Jamie Whincup, Mark Skaife and Greg Murphy. Then drivers hit the brakes hard into Australia's slowest corner at Turn 9, where they will attempt to out-brake each other to gain a position. . | Please note: Children's Policy: Children 3 years and under admitted for free if they sit on the lap of a full paying adult.
